Private crates from artifact_storage: NOTHING is vendored into this public repo anymore.

crates/gsvc-mount and crates/gsvc-codec are resolution-only placeholders (compile_error! bodies)
so the public tree builds and resolves standalone. The real sources live in the private
tensorlakeai/artifact_storage repo and are swapped in EPHEMERALLY, only for builds that enable
the features needing them (`mount`, `git-clone`):

  * locally:  just build-cli-full   — copies both crates' src/ from a sibling
              ../artifact_storage checkout for the build, restoring the placeholders afterward
  * CI:       .github/actions/vendor-private-crates — mints a short-lived GitHub App token
              (ARTIFACT_STORAGE_APP_ID / _PRIVATE_KEY), sparse-checks-out both crates' src/,
              and swaps them over the placeholders for the job only

The swapped source compiles against the PLACEHOLDER manifests, so each placeholder Cargo.toml's
dependency list must mirror the real crate's (crates/gsvc-mount/Cargo.toml and
crates/gsvc-codec/Cargo.toml in artifact_storage). If upstream dependencies change, update the
placeholder manifests in the same change that bumps the upstream.

Wire-format coupling still applies even without vendoring: the fast-clone client
(crates/cli/src/commands/git/fastclone.rs) and the ingest client
(crates/cloud-sdk/src/artifact_storage/ingest.rs) duplicate artifact_storage wire types
(FastCloneManifest and friends, ingest request/response shapes). If those change upstream, open
a companion PR here.
